WEBVTT

00:07.841 --> 00:11.218
♪ Oh, don't you remember ♪

00:11.428 --> 00:14.555
♪ A long time ago? ♪

00:14.764 --> 00:17.808
♪ Those two little babies ♪

00:18.018 --> 00:21.270
♪ Their names I don't know ♪

00:21.479 --> 00:24.398
♪ They strayed away ♪

00:24.607 --> 00:27.651
♪ One bright summer's day ♪

00:27.861 --> 00:30.946
♪ Those two little babies ♪

00:31.156 --> 00:34.158
♪ Got lost on their way ♪

00:34.367 --> 00:37.369
♪ Pretty babes in the wood ♪

00:37.579 --> 00:40.122
♪ Pretty babes in the wood. ♪

00:50.216 --> 00:52.384
Well, that's that then.

00:54.888 --> 00:57.222
Let's get a cab.
I can't face the walk.

01:00.560 --> 01:03.312
Reporter: Situated on
the outskirts of the city

01:03.521 --> 01:05.522
on the first day
of a weeklong series

01:05.732 --> 01:07.524
of special reports from Iraq

01:07.734 --> 01:10.944
to mark the fifth anniversary
of the Allied invasion.

01:11.154 --> 01:14.281
Five years on we've commissioned
the most comprehensive survey

01:14.491 --> 01:16.909
of the Iraqi people
ever undertaken,

01:17.118 --> 01:18.619
and it seems
like the nation

01:18.828 --> 01:21.538
is deeply pessimistic
about the future.

01:21.748 --> 01:25.042
The people are concerned
over the continued rise in violence

01:25.251 --> 01:27.461
and about the remaining
deep divides

01:27.670 --> 01:32.800
in their society.

01:33.009 --> 01:35.385
Garvey's here.

01:36.930 --> 01:39.223
Hey, big Bill!

01:39.432 --> 01:42.101
Can't keep a good man down,
can they?

01:42.310 --> 01:44.520
- Nice to see you, mate.
- Yeah, you too.

01:44.729 --> 01:46.605
Karl, make us some tea,
will you?

01:46.815 --> 01:48.315
I've gotta get out
of this monkey suit.

01:48.525 --> 01:49.942
Eh, full acquittal
though, yeah?

01:50.151 --> 01:52.402
- Get in! Come here.
- Thanks, man.

01:52.612 --> 01:55.114
I knew it was bollocks. They'd never
make that stick, would they?

01:55.323 --> 01:57.032
It's a fucking waste
of the taxpayers' money.

01:57.242 --> 01:59.785
Tell you what, it should be legalized
anyway, shouldn't it?

01:59.994 --> 02:01.703
- Yeah. Anyway, do you want some tea?
- Yeah.

02:01.913 --> 02:05.040
Maggie, would you make
Garvey some tea, please?

02:20.390 --> 02:21.974
Oh!

02:22.183 --> 02:23.976
(sighs)

02:24.185 --> 02:26.812
Jesus Christ, it's like
a fucking noose!

02:27.021 --> 02:29.273
Undo the knot.
Come here.

02:29.482 --> 02:32.609
- You're just tightening it.
- Fucking get it off me, man!

02:32.819 --> 02:35.237
Calm down.
Just let us have a look.

02:46.541 --> 02:48.500
How long has
he been here, Maggie?

02:48.710 --> 02:51.628
- He's had a sandwich.
- The disgusting fat locust.

02:51.838 --> 02:54.214
He's not fat.
He's got big bones, Bill.

02:54.424 --> 02:56.008
Well, he's peasant stock,
isn't he?

02:56.217 --> 03:00.596
Now, you know, it's all beer
and armchairs and TVs,

03:00.805 --> 03:03.307
and they're just a load of slobs.
It sickens me.

03:03.516 --> 03:06.351
His dad was a moron
as well.

03:07.478 --> 03:08.896
Good to see
a friendly face.

03:09.105 --> 03:10.981
I thought I'd pop in,
make sure you're all right.

03:11.191 --> 03:14.359
Tough four months
for you boys, I'd imagine.

03:14.569 --> 03:16.612
I just thought I'd come
and put your mind at rest.

03:16.821 --> 03:19.823
Everything's
running smoothly.

03:20.033 --> 03:21.825
I knew it was
all in safe hands.

03:22.035 --> 03:24.453
Well, I'll pop
to the little boys' room.

03:24.662 --> 03:26.747
Hey, you've put on
a bit of weight there, Garv.

03:26.956 --> 03:30.167
- I don't think so.
- I think you're getting a little bit heavier.

03:30.376 --> 03:33.170
Yeah, I can see it on the sides...
like handles.

03:33.379 --> 03:35.547
Right, thanks.

03:41.095 --> 03:43.096
- (door opens, closes)
- Maggie: Hello, Eric.

03:44.349 --> 03:46.350
Thanks.

03:47.727 --> 03:49.853
- Boys.
- Karl: Eric.

03:50.063 --> 03:52.648
- They gave you cake for the way out, did they?
- Karl: Oh, yeah.

03:52.857 --> 03:54.900
- Bill: All right, Eric?
- Yeah, I'm all right. You?

03:55.109 --> 03:57.277
- Yeah, not too bad now.
- Looks like a slab of concrete.

03:57.487 --> 03:59.488
Bill:
Yeah. Ah, it's all right.

03:59.697 --> 04:02.074
A little bit stale. Taste's a bit
like petrol, but it's okay.

04:02.283 --> 04:05.494
Looks like a dog's crapped on it.
Look at it.

04:05.703 --> 04:07.496
Garvey:
I quite liked it.

04:07.705 --> 04:09.665
- I thought it was all right.
- Oh, it's all right.

04:09.874 --> 04:11.500
Karl: If you swill it down
with enough tea,

04:11.709 --> 04:13.460
it'll be getting there,
you know.

04:13.670 --> 04:15.921
Eric: Well, don't break
your teeth on it.

04:16.130 --> 04:19.298
- Where'd you get it?
- I got it from the shop at the end of the road.

04:19.509 --> 04:22.010
- Those Pakis are thieves, man.
- You shouldn't say that...

04:22.220 --> 04:24.054
Pakis... anymore,
should you?

04:24.264 --> 04:27.724
- What's someone from Afghanistan?
- Uh, Afghani.

04:27.934 --> 04:30.060
- There you go.
- Yeah, that's true.

04:30.270 --> 04:32.562
- Brain of Britain.
- Karl: Yeah.

04:32.772 --> 04:35.274
This needs
painting over, Maggie.

04:35.483 --> 04:38.777
Yeah, everything's
a mess here.

04:38.987 --> 04:42.406
We can't be too conspicuous.
That's the golden rule.

04:44.325 --> 04:47.202
I wouldn't want a new house.
They've always got problems.

04:47.412 --> 04:50.622
You can't trust builders.

04:50.832 --> 04:54.376
This situation needs sorting out,
tidying up.

04:54.585 --> 04:58.338
Yeah. Like someone
close in, obviously.

04:58.548 --> 05:00.507
Yeah.

05:00.717 --> 05:02.509
Well, it's an informant
culture, isn't it?

05:02.719 --> 05:05.512
- Listen, about that money...
- Don't worry about that now.

05:05.722 --> 05:08.432
- That's good of you, Garv.
- That's all right.

05:08.641 --> 05:11.101
- I'll sort it out next week.
- No sweat.

05:11.311 --> 05:13.395
- I'll bring it round to your house.
- Or down the club.

05:13.604 --> 05:17.357
- Yeah, okay. Thanks, man.
- It's only money, isn't it?

05:19.569 --> 05:21.903
- Eric: Any beer about?
- Only what you brought, mate.

05:22.113 --> 05:24.072
I thought this was meant
to be a big party.

05:24.282 --> 05:27.242
Well, I'll pop down the offy.
Who wants what?

05:27.452 --> 05:32.205
Get us some whiskey,
some wine and some beer.

05:32.415 --> 05:33.957
And some matches
or a lighter.

05:34.167 --> 05:36.168
- No, a lighter.
- All right.

05:36.377 --> 05:38.253
- (Bill sighs)
- Okay.

05:38.463 --> 05:40.547
(phone ringing)

05:40.757 --> 05:43.300
Oh, fuck's sake.

05:48.014 --> 05:49.973
Where's Garvey getting
the booze from?

05:50.183 --> 05:52.517
- Bill: Just the offy over the road.
- Valda's coming round.

05:52.727 --> 05:54.728
- Bill: Who's coming over?
- Valda's coming round.

05:54.937 --> 05:57.647
Ah. That's his new bird.

05:57.857 --> 06:00.442
- Is it?
- Karl: I've been going out with her for a year.

06:00.651 --> 06:02.903
Bill: He's not been going out
with her for a year at all.

06:03.112 --> 06:05.197
How long have you
actually known her?

06:05.406 --> 06:07.783
- I haven't seen her in about six months.
- He hasn't seen her.

06:07.992 --> 06:11.411
- How long did you go out for?
- About a year... 10 months.

06:11.621 --> 06:14.164
Eric: I thought I heard
she done one.

06:14.374 --> 06:16.583
She did, but she just rung up.
She's coming round.

06:16.793 --> 06:19.795
Eric: Maybe she's pregnant.
(laughs)

06:20.004 --> 06:22.672
Bill:
Yeah, that's...

06:22.882 --> 06:25.175
that's extremely unlikely.

06:25.385 --> 06:27.177
I fast for January.

06:27.387 --> 06:31.098
No to poisons, no to drugs,
no food.

06:31.307 --> 06:32.849
I only allow myself tea.

06:33.059 --> 06:34.893
- Karl: And whiskey.
- Fucking hell, Bill.

06:35.103 --> 06:39.314
- I feel like a teenage tantric Superman.
- Yeah, so do I.

06:39.524 --> 06:41.274
Bill:
I'm a simple person.

06:41.484 --> 06:43.985
I like to reconnect
to the essentials.

06:45.488 --> 06:47.489
Go on.
Come on.

06:47.698 --> 06:49.616
Come on, Eric,
you're strong,

06:49.826 --> 06:51.284
you big-boned bastard.

06:51.494 --> 06:53.245
This is like tempered steel.
Come on.

06:53.454 --> 06:55.038
You do it to me,
then I'll do it to you.

06:55.248 --> 06:57.165
- Come on!
- Eric: Bad-tempered steel.

06:57.375 --> 06:59.418
Come on, Eric,
I'll let you have a go.

06:59.627 --> 07:02.295
- Come on, then.
- Let's have it.

07:02.505 --> 07:06.716
(all laughing)

07:06.926 --> 07:08.718
- Looks like a crossover.
- Go on, take a dig.

07:08.928 --> 07:11.179
- Take a fucking dig, Eric!
- Feel that.

07:11.389 --> 07:14.266
- It's soft as shite.
- Oh, you bastard!

07:14.475 --> 07:17.477
I forgot to pick
the kids up.

07:17.687 --> 07:20.647
- Bill: Oh, a man out of time.
- Shit.

07:20.857 --> 07:22.607
- Eric: What's happened?
- (phone vibrating)

07:22.817 --> 07:24.359
Oh, that's them
outside now.

07:24.569 --> 07:26.153
I'd better go.

07:28.614 --> 07:30.615
Bill:
Who's out there?

07:30.825 --> 07:33.034
- Karl: It's his missus.
- Bill: Is she coming in?

07:33.244 --> 07:34.536
No no no.
I'd better go.

07:34.745 --> 07:36.121
I gotta feed the kids
and that, but...

07:36.330 --> 07:37.914
Is that Helen?
I ain't seen her in years.

07:38.124 --> 07:39.499
Yeah yeah.
We gotta go.

07:39.709 --> 07:41.501
Well, uh, nice one.
Well done and everything.

07:41.711 --> 07:43.128
- Yeah, well done.
- Cheers, Garv.

07:43.337 --> 07:45.005
Yeah, see you later.

07:45.214 --> 07:46.882
See you, Maggie.

07:48.926 --> 07:50.469
See you, everyone.

07:50.678 --> 07:52.596
Cheers, Garv.
Have a good one, mate.

07:52.805 --> 07:54.431
She looks
absolutely furious.

07:54.640 --> 07:56.475
Bill: Give 'em a kiss
for me, Garv.

07:56.684 --> 07:58.810
Eric: She's fit...
his missus, mate.

07:59.020 --> 08:02.522
- Hoo-hoo.
- Karl: That's his old missus.

08:02.732 --> 08:05.650
His new missus is like
a hippo-croco-pig.

08:05.860 --> 08:08.945
(all chuckling)

08:09.155 --> 08:12.908
- Eric: A bit shortsighted.
- Looks a bit like him in a lady mirror.

08:13.117 --> 08:17.662
Bill: A female version of Garvey.
Can you imagine it?

08:17.872 --> 08:19.956
Give us one of those beers.
Oh, these are from Garvey.

08:20.166 --> 08:22.584
- Good old Garvin, eh?
- Bill: Yeah, cheers.

08:22.793 --> 08:25.962
- What a little superstar.
- Eric: He's shaken 'em up, hasn't he?

08:26.172 --> 08:29.090
He's totally fucking
depth-charged me.

08:29.300 --> 08:32.844
Why don't you just pour it
over the carpet?

08:33.054 --> 08:36.264
- (urinating)
- Karl. Oi.

08:36.474 --> 08:39.017
- Yeah? Hello, mate.
- Come here, I've got something to show you.

08:39.227 --> 08:42.312
- Hold on a second.
- By the way, when are you coming back to work?

08:42.522 --> 08:44.356
Soon. Just got to be
a bit careful, that's all.

08:44.565 --> 08:45.982
Well, you need
to hurry up.

08:46.192 --> 08:47.651
I'm running round
like a blue-ass fly.

08:47.860 --> 08:49.861
This thing don't
run itself, you know?

08:50.071 --> 08:51.988
- Everything's going all right though, yeah?
- Yeah.

08:52.198 --> 08:54.407
A bit of trouble in Whitehawk,
but otherwise shway shway.

08:54.617 --> 08:56.368
- Sweet.
- Come on out.

08:56.577 --> 08:59.287
I've got something
to show you.

08:59.497 --> 09:01.540
You are coming back
to work, aren't you?

09:01.749 --> 09:04.626
- Yeah, I told you. I'm coming in.
- (toilet flushes)

09:04.835 --> 09:08.338
So I don't have to run this whole
bloody operation by myself.

09:08.548 --> 09:10.840
Get in there. I've got something
to show you.

09:11.050 --> 09:13.093
- They're not gonna come up, are they?
- Doubt it.

09:13.302 --> 09:17.514
Oh, fucking hell! It's gone right through
the lining on my jacket.

09:17.723 --> 09:20.392
- What's that, Eric?
- A fucking gun, mate.

09:20.601 --> 09:22.310
- Got it off Don the Gun.
- Fuck off.

09:22.520 --> 09:24.437
That looks
totally real, man.

09:24.647 --> 09:28.525
(laughs) It is fucking totally real.
What are you talking about?

09:28.734 --> 09:30.569
- You serious?
- It's a real gun, yeah.

09:30.778 --> 09:33.780
- I just bought it for 200 quid.
- (gun clicking)

09:35.616 --> 09:37.492
Are you serious?
This is a real shooter?

09:37.702 --> 09:39.327
Yeah, it's a real shooter.
I just bought it.

09:39.537 --> 09:42.372
I just told you.
I need it, don't I?

09:44.584 --> 09:46.876
- What, you never seen a fucking gun before?
- Eric, Eric,

09:47.086 --> 09:48.628
are you out of your
fucking mind, mate?

09:48.838 --> 09:50.380
What?

09:50.590 --> 09:53.592
- Put it away and take it home.
- All right, all right.

09:53.801 --> 09:55.719
Well, he's not going
to see it, is he?

09:55.928 --> 09:58.138
I've just got my... I've just got
my prints all over a gun.

09:58.347 --> 10:00.390
Oh, for fuck's sake.
What are you, paranoid or what?

10:00.600 --> 10:02.684
What do you mean?
I've just come back from court.

10:02.893 --> 10:05.103
- (sniffing)
- (laughing) Oh, for Christ's sake, mate.

10:05.313 --> 10:07.731
- What's up with you?
- Has this been fired?

10:07.940 --> 10:10.150
Don't know.
Didn't ask.

10:10.359 --> 10:11.985
- Mate...
- (fabric rubbing)

10:12.194 --> 10:14.112
Look, give it to me.
I'll do that.

10:14.322 --> 10:16.698
- Come on...
- No, I'll do it. Thanks very much, Eric.

10:18.367 --> 10:19.951
It don't mean the old Bill
are going to come

10:20.161 --> 10:22.162
straight round now,
are they?

10:26.125 --> 10:27.959
Put it away.
I don't want to see it again.

10:28.169 --> 10:30.754
(laughing)

10:30.963 --> 10:33.423
Was he always such
an unctuous little prick...

10:33.633 --> 10:35.467
fucking Garvey?

10:35.676 --> 10:38.178
I'll say he's pretty consistent.
Why?

10:38.387 --> 10:40.972
I can't believe the old man's left him
running that fucking club.

10:41.182 --> 10:42.682
He's making
a fortune, man.

10:42.892 --> 10:44.726
I mean, he's just moved
into some flash new drum.

10:44.935 --> 10:47.020
Well, that should have
me and you on it.

10:47.229 --> 10:49.147
What can you say?
Bill is Bill.

10:49.357 --> 10:52.233
- How's he holding up?
- A bit rattled, I'd say.

10:52.443 --> 10:54.444
- Minor.
- What about you?

10:54.654 --> 10:57.864
Fine. I'm just trying
not to think about it.

10:58.074 --> 10:59.616
You know I'm right
behind you, don't you?

10:59.825 --> 11:01.785
(laughs)
What, leading from the rear, yeah?

11:01.994 --> 11:03.620
(laughing)

11:03.829 --> 11:06.289
I've got
your back, mate.

11:09.251 --> 11:11.086
Where's Garvey?

11:13.923 --> 11:15.715
If Benson had testified...

11:15.925 --> 11:17.759
(humming)

11:17.968 --> 11:19.761
It's all right, mate.
Calm down.

11:19.970 --> 11:21.846
It's all sorted.

11:22.056 --> 11:24.140
There you go.

11:24.350 --> 11:26.685
Oh, hang on. Here.

11:26.894 --> 11:29.938
- All right. Thanks, Karl.
- How you holding up?

11:35.611 --> 11:39.239
Well, they've shown their hand now,
haven't they?

11:39.448 --> 11:41.241
Yeah, we're home and dry
now though, right?

11:41.450 --> 11:43.993
(sighs)
Are we?

11:44.203 --> 11:46.746
I feel like I've been fighting this corner
forever, mate.

11:49.041 --> 11:51.000
40 years...
not a bad run.

11:53.379 --> 11:55.797
Oh, it was a run, was it?

11:56.006 --> 11:58.091
I mean, I was a smoker.

11:58.300 --> 12:02.011
I mean, I was a...
I was an artist, a poet.

12:02.221 --> 12:05.390
- The head.
- I was a head, you know.

12:06.767 --> 12:08.393
And I said I would do it.

12:08.602 --> 12:10.019
I started doing it

12:10.229 --> 12:13.314
and I could have
as much gear as I wanted,

12:13.524 --> 12:14.899
which was all
I was interested in.

12:15.109 --> 12:16.901
The funny thing was...
this is what I noticed

12:17.111 --> 12:19.154
first of all
when I got into it...

12:19.363 --> 12:23.825
was everybody else was into
making money, except me.

12:24.034 --> 12:26.619
I mean, me and Timothy Leary,
you know.

12:26.829 --> 12:30.373
I believed that this was a revolution
of consciousness

12:30.583 --> 12:33.251
and there was gonna be
an evolution taking place.

12:33.461 --> 12:35.712
And we were gonna find out
all these discoveries

12:35.921 --> 12:38.673
about the brain
and the future

12:38.883 --> 12:41.426
and how to be high
and stay high

12:41.635 --> 12:46.097
and how to be magical, how to live
in the world in this sort of new way.

12:46.307 --> 12:48.558
But all these other characters
basically were into bread.

12:48.768 --> 12:51.895
They made money and I
ended up just becoming

12:52.104 --> 12:54.439
just another criminal like them
because of force majeure.

12:54.648 --> 12:56.524
Because of Maggie and then
you and the rest of it,

12:56.734 --> 12:58.485
I had to do something.

12:58.694 --> 12:59.736
You know?

12:59.945 --> 13:02.280
Studied the "Tibetan
Book of the Dead."

13:02.490 --> 13:05.241
I learned how to control
my consciousness when I got into acid.

13:05.451 --> 13:06.659
I knew how to sort of...

13:06.869 --> 13:08.745
I did the full lotus,

13:08.954 --> 13:11.539
where you can get into
that little pyramid shape.

13:11.749 --> 13:15.668
And then it all starts to unfold,
you know, and curl up.

13:15.878 --> 13:19.172
It goes out the top of your head
and there you are, man.

13:19.381 --> 13:21.508
And you're like,
"Hey, I'm God.

13:21.717 --> 13:24.302
I am all men.
I can be Everyman.

13:24.512 --> 13:27.388
I'm no better,
no worse...

13:27.598 --> 13:29.724
certainly no worse than anyone else
in the world.

13:29.934 --> 13:32.560
I am Man.
I am Adam Kadmon."

13:32.770 --> 13:36.397
Three things... that's what I found
at the top level.

13:36.607 --> 13:38.441
You know what?
It's a triangle.

13:38.651 --> 13:41.611
It's goodness,
truth and beauty.

13:41.821 --> 13:44.155
And if things
aren't good,

13:44.365 --> 13:46.241
they're not true
and they're not beautiful.

13:46.450 --> 13:48.868
If it's good, it's also true
and beautiful.

13:49.078 --> 13:50.495
And that was the aim...

13:50.704 --> 13:55.291
to get that little triangle
in your forehead

13:55.501 --> 13:58.795
so you could see through
that lens of goodness, truth and beauty,

13:59.004 --> 14:02.173
and see the goodness and see
the truth and see the beauty.

14:02.383 --> 14:04.717
I've just become some sort of,
you know, grim recluse

14:04.927 --> 14:06.344
living in my diamond cave.

14:06.554 --> 14:09.931
There were good drugs
to start with,

14:10.140 --> 14:11.558
and then the freak-out
of the laws

14:11.767 --> 14:13.184
and the paranoia began.

14:13.394 --> 14:14.853
And everybody
splintered off

14:15.062 --> 14:17.188
and went into their rooms
and closed their curtains.

14:17.398 --> 14:20.483
And the communities
were all closed off from one another

14:20.693 --> 14:22.402
so nobody knew
what anybody else was doing.

14:22.611 --> 14:23.987
Everybody else
was just paranoid.

14:24.196 --> 14:27.949
You're only as good
as the people you're with.

