He reacted all wrong.
I'm good at reading people.

46:46.136 --> 46:47.595
He made a run for it.

46:47.805 --> 46:50.765
Not an unnatural response
in the circumstances.

46:50.974 --> 46:52.934
No, I'm talking about
your general aura.

46:53.143 --> 46:54.477
You know, he's a clown.
He's a fool.

46:54.686 --> 46:56.687
He's innocent.

46:56.897 --> 46:58.898
All right.

47:00.234 --> 47:02.276
Garv.

47:05.531 --> 47:07.740
- So you having a baby, eh?
- Yep.

47:07.950 --> 47:10.701
It's the best thing
that ever happened to me.

47:10.911 --> 47:13.329
I was trying for months
with Helen,

47:13.539 --> 47:15.957
but she had a problem
with her uterus.

47:16.166 --> 47:18.251
- Well, I did not know that, Garv.
- I'll tell you what.

47:18.460 --> 47:20.545
I want to ask you
something.

47:20.754 --> 47:22.922
On the night the twins
were conceived

47:23.131 --> 47:24.882
I made this, like,
roaring noise.

47:25.092 --> 47:26.676
I'd never
done that before.

47:26.885 --> 47:29.637
- Did you make a noise?
- Fuck knows.

47:29.847 --> 47:31.722
I don't know, but...

47:31.932 --> 47:34.225
So what's the name
of the lucky mom-to-be?

47:34.434 --> 47:36.727
- Valda.
- Valda.

47:36.937 --> 47:38.980
Valda Newland?

47:40.357 --> 47:41.774
- Why? Do you know her?
- Yeah yeah.

47:41.984 --> 47:44.694
She went out with my brother
a few months ago.

47:44.903 --> 47:47.071
- Really?
- Yeah yeah yeah.

47:47.281 --> 47:49.699
They were pen pals
together.

47:49.908 --> 47:51.325
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.

47:51.535 --> 47:54.161
She's had loads
of pen pals from prison.

47:54.371 --> 47:57.290
She's a... she's a lovely girl.
She's got a big heart.

47:57.499 --> 47:59.584
Well done.

48:04.882 --> 48:06.674
I'm painting tomorrow.

48:06.884 --> 48:08.843
- What, in here?
- Yeah, all around.

48:09.052 --> 48:11.220
- What color?
- Just white.

48:11.430 --> 48:13.347
Oh yeah, nice.
Fresh start.

48:13.557 --> 48:16.350
- Can you do me a favor for a second, Garv?
- Yeah, of course.

48:16.560 --> 48:19.645
- Can you just hold this up?
- Right.

48:19.855 --> 48:22.732
- Just there.
- Yeah.

48:22.941 --> 48:24.942
Actually,
I'm pretty knackered.

48:25.152 --> 48:26.777
You couldn't do us a tea,
could you, Karl?

48:26.987 --> 48:28.613
- Yeah, sure.
- What time is it?

48:28.822 --> 48:30.531
I've got
the kids tomorrow.

48:30.741 --> 48:33.451
Ah!

48:33.660 --> 48:35.912
Fuck your kids.

48:39.041 --> 48:41.709
(phone ringing)

48:41.919 --> 48:45.922
Eric, it's Karl.
Yeah.

48:46.131 --> 48:48.716
Any chance you could
possibly pop over?

48:50.761 --> 48:52.887
Yeah, I'm gonna need
your help with something.

48:53.096 --> 48:55.222
Come the back way, yeah?

48:55.432 --> 48:57.892
Wicked.
See you then.

49:04.274 --> 49:08.653
♪ 'Twas on one
summer's evening ♪

49:08.862 --> 49:12.615
♪ All in the month of May ♪

49:12.824 --> 49:15.743
♪ Down by a flowery garden ♪

49:15.953 --> 49:18.329
♪ Where Betsy did lay... ♪

49:18.538 --> 49:21.415
Fat sack of shit,
he's done my back in.

49:21.625 --> 49:25.002
- (coughing)
- Oh, fucking hell.

49:28.632 --> 49:31.842
Bill will have a full-blown fit
if he finds out about this.

49:32.052 --> 49:35.304
- I just don't want to hear his voice.
- Don't worry about it.

49:35.514 --> 49:37.765
Tell you what, this is
a blessing in disguise.

49:37.975 --> 49:39.684
For us anyway.

49:39.893 --> 49:42.186
Jesus Christ, there's probably
snakes in here.

49:42.396 --> 49:45.314
Yeah, we're gonna put another snake
in there in a minute.

49:45.524 --> 49:47.149
Mate, the ground
is well too hard.

49:47.359 --> 49:49.318
(groans)
We are never gonna do this.

49:49.528 --> 49:50.945
It's gonna take all day.

49:51.154 --> 49:53.572
Stop your fucking whingeing
and get on with it.

49:53.782 --> 49:55.825
I... what exactly
are you here to do?

49:56.034 --> 49:58.244
I'm here to help,
all right?

49:58.453 --> 50:00.913
- But you've only brought one shovel.
- Take a fucking turn!

50:01.123 --> 50:03.082
It's not a fucking
two-man shovel, is it?

50:03.291 --> 50:05.835
You take your turn,
then I'll take over.

50:06.044 --> 50:08.504
This is bollocks. We'll never get him
into this ground, mate.

50:08.714 --> 50:11.298
- We're just gonna have to leave him.
- We can't fucking leave him.

50:11.508 --> 50:13.217
We'll just have to fucking think of
something else.

50:13.427 --> 50:15.803
You have a fucking go.
Get in there and dig up...

50:16.013 --> 50:18.222
For fuck's sake.
You're fucking useless, you are.

50:18.432 --> 50:20.683
Here's a bit of fucking
soft ground here.

50:20.892 --> 50:22.643
There's no fucking
soft ground in there.

50:22.853 --> 50:24.437
Yes, there is.
It's fine.

50:24.646 --> 50:26.063
Eric:
Fucking coming out here

50:26.273 --> 50:28.232
to commune
with fucking nature.

50:30.986 --> 50:33.529
- Fucking hell.
- I don't know how you do this as a job.

50:33.739 --> 50:35.281
You're fucking
useless at it.

50:35.490 --> 50:36.782
Christ on a bike.
Look at you.

50:36.992 --> 50:38.325
Jesus, mate,
hold the fucking gate.

50:38.535 --> 50:41.787
I ought to fucking
knock you off, you ponce.

50:41.997 --> 50:44.081
(muttering)

50:44.291 --> 50:49.920
♪ Are you leaving
for the country? ♪

50:50.130 --> 50:55.926
♪ You say the city
brings you down ♪

50:56.136 --> 51:01.348
♪ Leave the iron clown
behind ♪

51:01.558 --> 51:06.062
♪ And feel the circus
moving on ♪

51:07.814 --> 51:12.735
♪ Are you leaving
for the country? ♪

51:12.944 --> 51:18.574
♪ I know a little
country town ♪

51:18.784 --> 51:23.079
♪ Where dogs are sleeping
in the cold ♪

51:23.288 --> 51:26.290
♪ And the flagpole's
falling down... ♪

51:26.500 --> 51:28.959
I wonder if it's gonna be
a girl or a boy.

51:29.169 --> 51:32.505
- What, your forthcoming progeny?
- Yeah.

51:32.714 --> 51:35.174
Science suggests
it'll be a girl.

51:38.386 --> 51:39.970
Why would it suggest that?

51:40.180 --> 51:43.307
Because the man determines
the sex of the child.

51:43.517 --> 51:47.436
So what diff...
what does that mean?

51:47.646 --> 51:50.898
- Well, you're that type.
- What type?

51:51.108 --> 51:52.900
Well, the type
that science talks about.

51:53.110 --> 51:55.611
What, the type of person
that only has girls?

51:55.821 --> 51:58.447
What, you think
I've only got girl sperm?

51:58.657 --> 52:01.575
Listen, man, you can't
argue with science.

52:05.122 --> 52:06.997
Who'd call
their kid Misery?

52:07.207 --> 52:09.208
(knocking)

52:11.086 --> 52:13.796
Dad, that's the door.

52:17.008 --> 52:18.717
Pa, that's the door.

52:18.927 --> 52:20.761
- (knocking)
- (sighs)

52:22.347 --> 52:24.723
Oh, fucking hell.
Don't get up.

52:29.312 --> 52:31.188
- All right, Karl.
- All right, Dave.

52:31.398 --> 52:33.274
- I hear you're getting married.
- That's right.

52:33.483 --> 52:37.319
(laughs)
Ducked 10 years and ended up getting life, eh?

52:37.529 --> 52:40.739
- All right, Bill.
- Hello, Dave.

52:40.949 --> 52:43.325
Garvey never went home
last night.

52:43.535 --> 52:45.161
Bill:
Oh, yeah? Is that official?

52:45.370 --> 52:47.663
Yeah. I've had his missus
on the phone to mine.

52:47.873 --> 52:49.957
After one night?
He's on a short leash.

52:50.167 --> 52:52.626
He never goes away,
does he?

52:52.836 --> 52:55.212
So, uh, was he here?

52:55.422 --> 52:59.008
- No.
- Karl: Not seen him.

52:59.217 --> 53:01.010
Well, who was here
last night?

53:01.219 --> 53:03.262
Just... just Pringle.

53:03.471 --> 53:06.098
Fucking hell.
Pringle.

53:06.308 --> 53:08.851
That's non-helpful.

53:09.060 --> 53:12.563
Right well, look,
if you see Garvey,

53:12.772 --> 53:14.064
you get him to give me
a bell, yeah?

53:14.274 --> 53:15.983
- Sure.
- Karl: Sure, will do.

53:16.193 --> 53:18.736
- Yeah, well, I...
- We'll see you later, man.

53:18.945 --> 53:21.155
I just don't want
his missus...

53:21.364 --> 53:24.033
- Bill: Take it easy, Dave.
...scaring up a big search party.

53:25.702 --> 53:27.912
I'll see you later.

53:28.121 --> 53:32.625
- Well, where do you think Garvey is?
- I don't know. He's...

53:35.420 --> 53:36.795
I don't like this.

53:37.005 --> 53:39.590
Do you think Eric's
into much with Garvey?

53:41.009 --> 53:43.260
Eric owes Garvey money.

53:43.470 --> 53:45.679
Quite a bit, knowing Eric.

53:45.889 --> 53:48.766
Why? What's wrong?
What's Eric got to do with it?

53:48.975 --> 53:51.936
Garvey's missing, that's all.
Nothing to worry about.

53:59.444 --> 54:03.322
I think someone must have picked him up
between here and his drum.

54:06.868 --> 54:10.329
- I can't go to prison, man.
- I know.

54:10.538 --> 54:12.539
I'll never come out.

54:22.050 --> 54:23.550
It's a confessional
culture, man.

54:23.760 --> 54:25.135
People just can't
shut up.

54:25.345 --> 54:28.389
Pringle will go then, yeah?

54:28.598 --> 54:31.934
- But who has he told?
- He lives with his mom.

54:32.143 --> 54:34.603
The kid's with
his ex-missus.

54:34.813 --> 54:36.981
It's unlikely he's gonna
say anything germane to her.

54:37.190 --> 54:39.525
Yeah, let's hope not, eh?
What do you think, Bill?

54:39.734 --> 54:42.111
(sighs)
I don't know.

54:42.320 --> 54:44.113
Mags?

54:44.322 --> 54:47.199
Pringle tells his war stories
to whoever'll listen.

54:47.409 --> 54:49.410
The mom's a notorious
chatterbox.

54:49.619 --> 54:51.829
Just to be safe then, yeah?

54:52.038 --> 54:55.332
Okay.
This is on me then, yeah?

54:57.043 --> 54:58.961
I'll deal with Pringle
and his people.

54:59.170 --> 55:01.463
This is turning into
a right fucking massacre.

55:01.673 --> 55:04.341
- Yay.
- What about the kid? He's got a kid.

55:04.551 --> 55:07.094
Yeah, the kid's about two.
He can't even talk, can he?

55:07.304 --> 55:09.179
I mean, what's going
to happen to the kid?

55:09.389 --> 55:11.765
He'll probably end up getting sent
to a decent school.

55:11.975 --> 55:15.728
Would you want Pringle
as your old man?

55:15.937 --> 55:18.022
Can't believe they've brought this
on themselves.

55:18.231 --> 55:20.441
They're so selfish.

55:20.650 --> 55:22.818
Disappearances
and accidents, Eric.

55:23.028 --> 55:24.320
No showboating.

55:24.529 --> 55:28.032
Bill, come on.

55:32.620 --> 55:34.496
Here, Pa.

55:34.706 --> 55:37.207
- Cheers.
- Eric: To Garvey.

55:37.417 --> 55:39.543
All:
Garvey.

55:41.296 --> 55:44.548
- Bill: And Pringle.
- Yeah, and Pringle.

55:44.758 --> 55:47.718
All:
Pringle.

55:47.927 --> 55:50.387
- A shame about his kid.
- Yeah.

55:50.597 --> 55:53.932
Don't think about it.
I'm not.

55:54.142 --> 55:55.934
Still...

55:56.144 --> 55:57.353
that's the way
it goes, isn't it?

55:57.562 --> 55:59.646
A lot of children die.

55:59.856 --> 56:02.191
What time is it?

56:02.400 --> 56:04.276
What, now?

56:04.486 --> 56:07.488
It's about 25 past 4:00.

56:07.697 --> 56:11.241
- Why, have you got an appointment?
- Nah, I was just wondering.

56:16.206 --> 56:19.875
(waves crashing)

56:20.085 --> 56:23.670
- It's just nice to be out of the house.
- Mm.

56:26.007 --> 56:28.133
Sometimes don't you think
you could just walk

56:28.343 --> 56:31.470
straight out into the sea
and never come back?

56:34.516 --> 56:39.645
You're full of cheery little introspective
observations today.

56:39.854 --> 56:42.439
What did you want to be
when you grew up?

56:45.110 --> 56:47.945
Nothing.

56:48.154 --> 56:50.406
How much
do you love me?

57:03.878 --> 57:06.380
Rah!

57:08.299 --> 57:09.591
Eric:
Oi, Pringle.

57:09.801 --> 57:11.552
- You all right, mate?
- How you doing?

57:11.761 --> 57:13.345
- I've got a little job for you.
- Oh, yeah?

57:13.555 --> 57:15.139
- Yeah. You up for it?
- Yeah, nice.

57:15.348 --> 57:17.099
Come on, mate.

57:17.308 --> 57:18.725
Come on, jump in.

57:18.935 --> 57:20.436
It's lovely here, isn't it?

57:20.645 --> 57:22.521
- Stinks of shit, mate.
- Yeah.

57:22.730 --> 57:24.398
But I like those
fresh country smells.

57:24.607 --> 57:28.026
- You know what I mean?
- So what's this all about?

57:28.236 --> 57:30.988
Just gotta see a geezer over here.
Don't worry about it.

57:31.197 --> 57:33.824
- Whereabouts?
- Just over here.

57:34.033 --> 57:37.411
- By this caravan?
- No no, just by the side of the caravan.

57:37.620 --> 57:40.289
Nothing to worry about.
Don't worry.

57:41.958 --> 57:44.376
(laughs)

57:44.586 --> 57:47.004
Aw, come on, man.
What about my son?

57:47.213 --> 57:50.591
Oh, don't fucking cry,
mate. Oi!

57:50.800 --> 57:53.260
Oh, for fuck's sake, where do you think
you're going?

57:58.475 --> 58:00.309
(dog barking)

58:00.518 --> 58:03.395
Twat.

58:12.363 --> 58:17.034
Ma, I'm gonna move out.

58:17.243 --> 58:20.412
I thought Valda
was gonna move in here.

58:20.622 --> 58:23.207
Val wants our own space.
I think she's right.

58:23.416 --> 58:26.335
Well, you'll need help with the baby.
I mean, she looks frail.

58:26.544 --> 58:29.379
I'm having a kid.
I can't go to prison.

58:29.589 --> 58:33.509
Nobody's going to prison
and you're going to do as you're told.

58:35.094 --> 58:36.803
I don't want to do
any of this anymore.

58:37.013 --> 58:39.014
I just want to be a...

58:39.224 --> 58:41.225
I just want to be
a normal dad.

58:44.812 --> 58:46.647
- Mrs. Pringle?
- Yeah?

58:46.856 --> 58:48.482
I'm a friend
of your son's.

58:48.691 --> 58:50.400
Eric, yeah?
You remember me?

58:50.610 --> 58:52.945
- Is he all right?
- Yeah, he's fine, yeah.

58:53.154 --> 58:55.072
You been shopping?
You bought anything nice?

58:55.281 --> 58:57.032
Oh, just a few bits
for the kids, you know.

58:57.242 --> 58:59.701
- Trying to cut back a bit these days.
- Yeah, times is tight.

58:59.911 --> 59:02.204
- We've all got too much anyway, haven't we?
- That is true.

59:02.413 --> 59:04.790
I can't believe how much he looks
like his old dad.

59:04.999 --> 59:06.792
Yeah, poor little thing, eh?
(laughing)

59:07.001 --> 59:08.961
What time is this bus
coming then?

59:09.170 --> 59:12.339
- (screams)
- (tires screeching)

59:14.759 --> 59:17.594
- And the fat man?
- Oh, he's really shit the bed on this one, mate.

59:17.804 --> 59:20.347
Looked all over for him...
high and low, here and there.

59:20.557 --> 59:22.599
- Yeah?
- Pie shop.

59:22.809 --> 59:26.603
- He's gone.
- Yeah, I thought so. I had a feeling.

59:26.813 --> 59:28.647
- Bill: You want a whiskey?
- Yeah, lovely.

59:28.856 --> 59:31.316
What's going on, you know,
with the business and...

59:31.526 --> 59:33.235
and the club?

59:33.444 --> 59:36.572
Well, looks like I'm gonna need
a new manager, doesn't it?

59:36.781 --> 59:39.575
Yeah, I've been having
a little think about that.

59:39.784 --> 59:41.493
- Cheers.
- Yeah?

59:41.703 --> 59:46.290
Yeah, just, you know,
about who to put in there.

59:46.499 --> 59:48.625
- Yeah.
- And then I thought,

59:48.835 --> 59:50.586
I ran Foxy's, didn't I?

59:50.795 --> 59:52.629
- For 10 years down in Eastbourne.
- Oh, yeah.

59:52.839 --> 59:55.507
We did a great job down there, mate.
Great job.

59:55.717 --> 59:57.384
Yeah yeah yeah yeah.

59:57.594 --> 01:00:00.178
- That was a long time ago, Eric.
- I mean me and Karl...

01:00:00.388 --> 01:00:03.140
- it would keep us busy.
- Karl's a very busy boy.

01:00:03.349 --> 01:00:07.394
Yeah. No, he's probably too busy,
but I've still got time.

01:00:07.604 --> 01:00:09.855
I could help out
down there.

01:00:10.064 --> 01:00:13.609
I thought it'd, like,
dovetail with the business.

01:00:15.778 --> 01:00:19.615
Yeah. Well, I mean,
obviously I understand

01:00:19.824 --> 01:00:23.535
where you're coming from,
but I'll leave it with you.

01:00:23.745 --> 01:00:26.038
Have a little think
about it, mate.

01:00:26.247 --> 01:00:27.998
I'll tell you what,
I'll think about it.

01:00:28.207 --> 01:00:31.335
Yeah yeah, nice nice.
Okay. So what?

01:00:31.544 --> 01:00:34.421
I'll call you later maybe,
have a chat?

01:00:36.424 --> 01:00:39.343
I mean, it's a good idea...
a good idea, Bill,

01:00:39.552 --> 01:00:43.263
because I feel that
the club could be...

01:00:43.473 --> 01:00:45.682
I've got some ideas
for the club,

01:00:45.892 --> 01:00:47.184
strategic ideas.

01:00:47.393 --> 01:00:50.103
(blues music playing)

01:00:53.650 --> 01:00:56.109
Running a club.
(scoffs)

01:00:58.655 --> 01:01:01.198
- Helen.
- Where is he?

01:01:01.407 --> 01:01:03.575
- Bill?
- My husband!

01:01:03.785 --> 01:01:05.202
How should I know?
I'm cooking.

01:01:05.411 --> 01:01:07.579
- I just want his body!
- Shh, keep it down.

01:01:07.789 --> 01:01:10.332
- Whatever's left!
- Keep it down, keep it down.

01:01:10.541 --> 01:01:12.459
I don't want him lying
out there in a ditch!

01:01:12.669 --> 01:01:14.628
- Keep it... keep it...
- I won't keep it down!

01:01:14.837 --> 01:01:19.174
Getting eaten up by...
by things and foxes, you fuck.

01:01:19.384 --> 01:01:21.093
Look, you're under
a lot of stress, Helen.

01:01:21.302 --> 01:01:23.136
I understand it, but it's totally
out of order.

01:01:23.346 --> 01:01:26.264
You cold bitch.
You're just like your father.

01:01:26.474 --> 01:01:28.475
- Get out of here.
- You'll end up just like him.

01:01:28.685 --> 01:01:30.811
(shouting, banging)

01:01:31.020 --> 01:01:32.479
Unacceptable, Bill.

01:01:32.689 --> 01:01:35.899
I told you when we started this...
no drama.

01:01:36.109 --> 01:01:38.527
She's a prime candidate
for shock treatment.

01:01:38.736 --> 01:01:42.781
- Nobody is gonna listen to her ravings.
- Not listen?

01:01:42.990 --> 01:01:45.158
I am surprised they didn't hear that
in fucking Kent.

01:01:45.368 --> 01:01:47.577
Why'd she start talking
about my dad?

01:01:47.787 --> 01:01:50.914
Why'd she have to say that?

01:02:18.276 --> 01:02:20.777
Karl: Oh, Jonny.
How you doing, buddy?

01:02:20.987 --> 01:02:23.989
(chattering)

01:02:34.751 --> 01:02:37.210
- Jonny.
- Good journey, yeah?

01:02:37.420 --> 01:02:40.338
Not really, no.

01:02:40.548 --> 01:02:43.925
Well, what brings you
all the way down from London, Jon?

01:02:45.595 --> 01:02:48.597
I told Jacob I didn't
want to come down, Bill.

01:02:48.806 --> 01:02:51.183
Well, why didn't
he come down himself?

01:02:53.352 --> 01:02:58.315
Jacob's a little, uh,
disappointed in you, Bill.

01:03:01.027 --> 01:03:05.238
A general vibe
of confusion

01:03:05.448 --> 01:03:08.283
and carnage coming
from your end.

01:03:08.493 --> 01:03:12.120
- There's been a few ructions, but it's evening out.
- Is it?

